920.question: When they say "comparable performance", how much of a performance drop do these new embeddings result in?
920.response: {'Answer': 'On Link Prediction tasks, the performance drop associated with the new embeddings is 1.2 for MRR (from 31.6 to 30.4), 10 for MR (from 121.9 to 111.9), and -1.5 for Hits@10 (from 48.3 to 46.8). On Triple Classification tasks, the performance actually improves by 0.3 for AUC (from 72.9 to 73.2) and 4.4 for Accuracy (from 63.2 to 67.6).'}
920.answer: Performance was comparable, with the proposed method quite close and sometimes exceeding performance of baseline method.
